  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Niger State Urban Technical Support Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to provide technical
expertise to the Niger State Government to implement the New Urban Agenda
through the development of a sub national urban policy for the state along with
integrated and territorial plans for Minna and Suleja Emirates, with particular
attention being paid to capacity enhancement, peer to peer learning to enhance
performance of the different stakeholders. Advisory services on urban-rural
linkages and smart city strategies with particular reference to youth, gender
and human rights issues will be undertaken.

The
development of the state urban policy and the integrated plans for Minna and
Suleja Emirates will largely transform their social, economic and environmental
conditions of Niger state&apos;s urban population by promoting safe and habitable
cities in Niger State where the benefits of sustainable urbanization including strengthened
legislative/regulatory frameworks, improved infrastructure services, enhanced
human and economic capacities and inclusive governance processes. It will
ensure safe and habitable cities Niger state cities.</narrative>
  </description>
